        },
        "subject": "LU-1682 mgc: cld refcount remains",
        "message": "LU-1682 mgc: cld refcount remains\n\nmgc_blocking_ast will never be called when ldlm_cli_enqueue failed\nto allocate memory for new ldlm_lock. As a result, it causes that\na cld refcount never go back to 0.\nThis patch decreases cld refcount when the allocation failure\noccured\n\nSigned-off-by: Hiroya Nozaki <nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com>\nChange-Id: I7cc6552771adafcedca5b2e591427bf16f5a3d46\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
